cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

This paper involves the development of a deep learning algorithm for medical imaging, specifically for breast cancer detection on screening mammograms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of an end-to-end training approach and the efficient leveraging of training datasets, which suggests a focus on machine learning techniques. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with medical imaging databases and the transferability of the algorithm to different platforms, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
